name: Hypnos monopterygius
description: The marine species Hypnos monopterygius is a marine species. It is found in Port Jackson, Australia, 12 km N Richmond River. This species inhabits shallow coastal waters.

name: Aurora Sailfin Reeffish
description: The Aurora Sailfin Reeffish (Aurantichthys prismatica) is a reef-dwelling fish known for its large sail-like dorsal fin and intense iridescent colors. Its prism-like scales reflect blues, reds, and oranges, helping it blend with filtered reef light. The elongated fins are used for display and predator intimidation, while its large eyes suggest adaptation to low-light reef environments. It is a slow, highly maneuverable swimmer that feeds on plankton and small crustaceans.
